{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["iwl_dev_info_table"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The iwlwifi driver for Intel Wireless-AC 9260 (device ID 0x2526) is missing PCI subdevice entries in the iwl_dev_info_table. The bug report indicates missing subdevice entries for 0x401D (or possibly 0x0401D), 0x4018, and 0x401C. While the iwl_hw_card_ids table has a catch-all entry for device 0x2526 with PCI_ANY_ID (line 599), the iwl_dev_info_table lacks specific entries for these subdevices. These entries are required for proper device configuration and firmware selection. The iwl_dev_info_table is consulted during the PCI probe function (iwl_pci_probe) to match device-specific configurations. Without these entries, the device will fall back to the default configuration, which doesn't load the appropriate firmware, resulting in the reported firmware loading failure. The missing entries should be added around line 995 in the iwl_dev_info_table with appropriate firmware configurations (likely iwl9560_2ac_160_cfg based on the pattern of similar 0x40xx subdevices like 0x4030)."
}

